              "text_crqjma": {
                "type": "text",
                "settings": {
                  "visibility": "always-display",
                  "text": "<p>We’ve all been there: standing under the harsh fluorescent lights of a bathroom vanity, layering product upon product, only to realize that the more we try to \"fix,\" the more we seem to mask the very features we once loved. It’s a quiet, daily exhaustion—a cycle of buying, applying, and eventually scrubbing away a version of ourselves that feels increasingly heavy and artificial.</p>",
